1
00:00:14,067 --> 00:00:16,767
<i>It's just because of the surgery
and your mother's illness.</i>

2
00:00:16,900 --> 00:00:18,767
<i> I believe the day will come</i>

3
00:00:18,900 --> 00:00:21,133
<i>when she remembers that she
already forgave me.</i>

4
00:00:21,267 --> 00:00:23,833
<i>We need the help
of other therapists.</i>

5
00:00:23,967 --> 00:00:26,733
<i>You mean she'll be able
to function normally again?</i>

6
00:00:26,867 --> 00:00:28,467
<i>- Yes.
- Miss Felma...</i>

7
00:00:28,600 --> 00:00:31,133
<i>I'd like you to meet
your physical therapist,</i>

8
00:00:31,267 --> 00:00:32,633
<i> Joselito Cañares.</i>

9
00:00:32,767 --> 00:00:34,100
<i> Good morning, Miss Felma.</i>

10
00:00:34,267 --> 00:00:36,700
<i>We'll start
with simple exercises.</i>

11
00:00:36,833 --> 00:00:37,467
<i> Sitting up.</i>

12
00:00:37,600 --> 00:00:38,467
<i> Standing...</i>

13
00:00:38,600 --> 00:00:41,533
<i>This way, we help the body
and brain</i>

14
00:00:41,667 --> 00:00:43,100
<i> learn to work together again.</i>

15
00:00:43,233 --> 00:00:44,300
<i> My love?</i>

16
00:00:44,433 --> 00:00:45,967
<i> Sorry.</i>

17
00:00:48,933 --> 00:00:50,333
Do you even have to ask?

18
00:00:51,167 --> 00:00:54,567
I get commendations
at work all the time.

19
00:00:55,600 --> 00:00:57,333
And you know that, Hazel.

20
00:00:59,133 --> 00:01:01,233
How's Flirty Felma as a patient?

21
00:01:05,433 --> 00:01:06,833
She seems...

22
00:01:07,900 --> 00:01:10,300
easy to win over.

23
00:01:10,433 --> 00:01:11,433
And I think...

24
00:01:11,567 --> 00:01:13,600
she trusts me completely.

25
00:01:19,967 --> 00:01:21,033
Very good.

26
00:01:22,800 --> 00:01:24,000
Just remember...

27
00:01:25,300 --> 00:01:29,200
you're doing all this
for our daughter, Jessica.

28
00:01:30,500 --> 00:01:33,167
Continue playing along
with Felma...

29
00:01:33,300 --> 00:01:35,500
and her family.

30
00:01:35,633 --> 00:01:37,300
Make her caregivers...

31
00:01:37,433 --> 00:01:39,933
believe they can trust you.

32
00:01:41,900 --> 00:01:42,700
Of course.

33
00:01:44,467 --> 00:01:46,867
I know exactly what to do.

34
00:01:47,000 --> 00:01:48,567
And most importantly,

35
00:01:49,600 --> 00:01:52,267
they can't find out that we know
each other.

36
00:01:53,300 --> 00:01:55,700
And that you're Jessica's
real father.

37
00:02:09,000 --> 00:02:09,967
<i> Excuse me.</i>

38
00:02:10,100 --> 00:02:11,000
<i> Yes?</i>

39
00:02:12,467 --> 00:02:13,367
<i> Miss...</i>

40
00:02:14,533 --> 00:02:18,267
<i>by any chance,
do you have a PT named...</i>

41
00:02:18,933 --> 00:02:21,033
<i> Joselito Cañares?</i>

42
00:02:21,167 --> 00:02:23,733
<i> My friend mentioned him.</i>

43
00:02:23,867 --> 00:02:28,033
<i>She recommended him to someone
who was admitted here.</i>

44
00:02:28,167 --> 00:02:30,600
<i> What's the patient's name?</i>

45
00:02:30,733 --> 00:02:32,567
<i>- Felma Ruiz.
- Felma Ruiz.</i>

46
00:02:32,700 --> 00:02:34,100
<i> Please wait. I'll check.</i>

47
00:02:38,333 --> 00:02:40,367
<i> Based on our records,</i>

48
00:02:40,500 --> 00:02:42,633
<i>there's no PT assigned
to her yet.</i>

49
00:02:42,767 --> 00:02:45,767
<i>Her doctor needs to make
the referral.</i>

50
00:02:45,900 --> 00:02:49,200
<i>But you do have a PT named
Joselito Canares?</i>

51
00:02:49,367 --> 00:02:50,867
<i> Sir Jojo?</i>

52
00:03:00,400 --> 00:03:01,267
<i> Hazel?</i>

53
00:03:04,200 --> 00:03:05,400
<i> Is that really you?</i>

54
00:03:13,833 --> 00:03:15,867
<i>I've been looking for you
for so long.</i>

55
00:03:25,433 --> 00:03:27,400
<i> I'm really, really sorry...</i>

56
00:03:28,467 --> 00:03:29,467
<i> Hazel.</i>

57
00:03:30,433 --> 00:03:34,100
<i> I was such a jerk,</i>

58
00:03:34,600 --> 00:03:37,500
<i>leaving you behind
in Saudi Arabia..</i>

59
00:03:38,300 --> 00:03:40,067
<i>when I found out
you were pregnant.</i>

60
00:03:41,100 --> 00:03:43,233
<i> I was so immature.</i>

61
00:03:43,367 --> 00:03:46,600
<i>I didn't know where my life
was going.</i>

62
00:03:49,400 --> 00:03:51,333
<i> I was scared. I'll admit it.</i>

63
00:03:51,467 --> 00:03:55,400
<i>Scared of the responsibility
of being a father, because...</i>

64
00:03:55,567 --> 00:03:57,867
<i> I didn't know how.</i>

65
00:03:58,900 --> 00:03:59,867
<i> So...</i>

66
00:04:01,133 --> 00:04:02,933
<i>I decided to return
to the Philippines.</i>

67
00:04:04,233 --> 00:04:08,267
<i>After a few years,
I applied to the US...</i>

68
00:04:08,400 --> 00:04:09,967
<i>and was lucky to become
a physical therapist.</i>

69
00:04:11,167 --> 00:04:12,600
<i> I became successful.</i>

70
00:04:12,733 --> 00:04:13,467
<i> But..</i>

71
00:04:14,633 --> 00:04:17,067
<i> I was never at peace...</i>

72
00:04:17,200 --> 00:04:19,833
<i>because I abandoned you
and our child.</i>

73
00:04:22,767 --> 00:04:24,500
<i> Believe it or not...</i>

74
00:04:26,667 --> 00:04:27,933
<i> I looked for you.</i>

75
00:04:29,033 --> 00:04:31,400
<i>I even went back
to Saudi Arabia,</i>

76
00:04:31,533 --> 00:04:34,867
<i>but no one knew where you were.</i>

77
00:04:35,000 --> 00:04:37,767
<i>I looked for your best friend,
Alice.</i>

78
00:04:37,900 --> 00:04:39,367
<i> But to no avail.</i>

79
00:04:39,500 --> 00:04:42,267
<i>I even went back
to the old hospital,</i>

80
00:04:42,400 --> 00:04:45,467
<i>but they wouldn't give me
any details...</i>

81
00:04:45,600 --> 00:04:48,200
<i>because of staff
confidentiality.</i>

82
00:04:48,333 --> 00:04:51,467
<i>There were so many
Hazel's online.</i>

83
00:04:51,600 --> 00:04:53,333
<i> I couldn't find you.</i>

84
00:04:53,467 --> 00:04:55,667
<i> I didn't know...</i>

85
00:04:55,800 --> 00:04:59,367
<i>your last name
if you got married.</i>

86
00:04:59,500 --> 00:05:00,000
<i> Or...</i>

87
00:05:01,033 --> 00:05:02,467
<i> if you blocked me.</i>

88
00:05:06,667 --> 00:05:07,900
<i> Of course.</i>

89
00:05:11,967 --> 00:05:13,267
<i> So...</i>

90
00:05:14,100 --> 00:05:15,867
<i> I decided to...</i>

91
00:05:16,200 --> 00:05:17,900
<i>settle here in the Philippines.</i>

92
00:05:20,200 --> 00:05:22,100
<i> And this is where I find you.</i>

93
00:05:24,900 --> 00:05:28,700
<i> Hazel, I know you're...</i>

94
00:05:28,833 --> 00:05:33,867
<i> still furious at me.</i>

95
00:05:34,000 --> 00:05:35,500
<i> But I'm hoping...</i>

96
00:05:35,667 --> 00:05:37,733
<i> you'll give me a chance....</i>

97
00:05:39,067 --> 00:05:40,733
<i>to make it up to you
and our child.</i>

98
00:05:41,933 --> 00:05:46,367
<i> If I'm not mistaken...</i>

99
00:05:46,500 --> 00:05:49,000
<i> she's about 18 now.</i>

100
00:05:49,133 --> 00:05:50,200
<i> Am I right?</i>

101
00:05:53,767 --> 00:05:55,633
<i> Is she a boy or a girl?</i>

102
00:05:59,100 --> 00:06:00,133
<i> A girl.</i>

103
00:06:01,667 --> 00:06:02,833
<i> Her name is Jessica.</i>

104
00:06:04,100 --> 00:06:04,967
<i> Wow.</i>

105
00:06:07,133 --> 00:06:09,833
<i> That's a beautiful name.</i>

106
00:06:10,000 --> 00:06:13,600
<i>Do you have a picture of her?
Can I see...</i>

107
00:06:14,400 --> 00:06:16,300
<i> who she looks like?</i>

108
00:06:26,833 --> 00:06:27,767
<i> Wow...</i>

109
00:06:28,667 --> 00:06:29,567
<i> she's beautiful.</i>

110
00:06:31,000 --> 00:06:32,467
<i> She looks like both of us.</i>

111
00:06:34,633 --> 00:06:35,500
<i> Hazel...</i>

112
00:06:37,233 --> 00:06:38,500
<i> I'm begging you.</i>

113
00:06:39,900 --> 00:06:41,200
<i> Can I see her today?</i>

114
00:06:42,033 --> 00:06:43,333
<i> Even after my shift?</i>

115
00:06:44,267 --> 00:06:45,333
<i> Please?</i>

116
00:06:49,767 --> 00:06:50,900
<i> She's gone.</i>

117
00:06:53,733 --> 00:06:54,500
<i> Jojo...</i>

118
00:06:56,667 --> 00:06:58,467
<i> our daughter is dead.</i>

119
00:06:59,567 --> 00:07:00,600
<i> What?</i>

120
00:07:12,467 --> 00:07:15,333
My goodness, my love.

121
00:07:16,300 --> 00:07:20,000
I pushed you away.

122
00:07:20,833 --> 00:07:28,400
I said awful things to you.

123
00:07:30,600 --> 00:07:36,467
I was completely out of line.

124
00:07:36,600 --> 00:07:42,200
I was horrible.

125
00:07:44,133 --> 00:07:46,233
Felma, this isn't your fault,
okay?

126
00:07:47,000 --> 00:07:48,533
None of it is.

127
00:07:48,700 --> 00:07:51,500
The doctor said it's just part
of the surgery.

128
00:07:52,100 --> 00:07:55,567
So don't be ashamed
or feel small, all right?

129
00:07:58,300 --> 00:07:59,900
Yes.

130
00:08:00,933 --> 00:08:02,833
By God's mercy...

131
00:08:04,300 --> 00:08:08,667
and grace.

132
00:08:09,733 --> 00:08:12,233
And I still have a promise
to you.

133
00:08:12,367 --> 00:08:16,433
The annulment has to go through,
then we'll get married, right?

134
00:08:19,100 --> 00:08:22,700
Are you sure...

135
00:08:23,500 --> 00:08:29,700
you'll still marry me...

136
00:08:30,600 --> 00:08:40,200
even if my memories
never come back?

137
00:08:42,100 --> 00:08:44,767
But I hope...

138
00:08:45,767 --> 00:08:49,533
that doesn't happen.

139
00:08:50,800 --> 00:08:52,000
Don't worry.

140
00:08:52,933 --> 00:08:55,700
I'll never get tired
of reminding you of everything,

141
00:08:56,700 --> 00:08:59,033
especially our happy memories.

142
00:09:13,767 --> 00:09:16,800
They will pay for what they did
to you and to my child.

143
00:09:17,267 --> 00:09:18,800
My child...

144
00:09:29,000 --> 00:09:30,367
<i> Papa's here now.</i>

145
00:09:32,367 --> 00:09:33,600
<i> But I was a fool.</i>

146
00:09:35,467 --> 00:09:36,900
<i> I'm too late.</i>

147
00:09:39,700 --> 00:09:42,233
<i>We never even got
the chance...</i>

148
00:09:44,267 --> 00:09:46,200
<i> to know each other.</i>

149
00:09:47,367 --> 00:09:50,133
<i> To make memories together.</i>

150
00:10:00,200 --> 00:10:01,500
<i> I'm sorry, Hazel.</i>

151
00:10:03,267 --> 00:10:05,400
<i>There's something I never told
you before.</i>

152
00:10:09,167 --> 00:10:10,500
<i> I thought...</i>

153
00:10:12,167 --> 00:10:15,633
<i>my illness back then was already
my karma.</i>

154
00:10:16,600 --> 00:10:18,933
<i>That I'd never be able to have
a child.</i>

155
00:10:19,833 --> 00:10:23,100
<i>That's why I tried so hard
to find you.</i>

156
00:10:26,100 --> 00:10:28,267
<i> Jessica was my only chance...</i>

157
00:10:28,600 --> 00:10:30,200
<i> to experience being...</i>

158
00:10:31,567 --> 00:10:32,667
<i> a father.</i>

159
00:10:33,567 --> 00:10:36,500
<i>But this punishment hurts more.</i>

160
00:10:37,133 --> 00:10:40,067
<i> Never seeing your child...</i>

161
00:10:40,600 --> 00:10:42,000
<i> never getting to know her.</i>

162
00:10:43,333 --> 00:10:44,467
<i> Honestly...</i>

163
00:10:48,400 --> 00:10:50,567
<i> I want to curse you.</i>

164
00:10:51,533 --> 00:10:52,700
<i> Blame you.</i>

165
00:10:54,000 --> 00:10:55,000
<i> Hurt you,</i>

166
00:10:56,400 --> 00:10:58,467
<i>right here at our child's grave.</i>

167
00:10:59,200 --> 00:11:00,800
<i> Just so I could get even...</i>

168
00:11:02,033 --> 00:11:05,100
<i>for everything you put us
through.</i>

169
00:11:09,167 --> 00:11:11,933
<i>We suffered so much after you
left us.</i>

170
00:11:15,700 --> 00:11:18,200
<i>I was forced to marry a man I
didn't love...</i>

171
00:11:19,033 --> 00:11:20,633
<i>just so Jessica would have
a father.</i>

172
00:11:22,133 --> 00:11:24,333
<i>So I wouldn't be punished
in Saudi Arabia.</i>

173
00:11:25,933 --> 00:11:27,633
<i> As Jessica grew up,</i>

174
00:11:28,533 --> 00:11:29,933
<i> I realized...</i>

175
00:11:31,200 --> 00:11:33,367
<i> how wrong that decision was.</i>

176
00:11:35,567 --> 00:11:37,400
<i> Manuel was cruel.</i>

177
00:11:38,533 --> 00:11:40,100
<i> And later, I found out...</i>

178
00:11:41,533 --> 00:11:43,633
<i> he already had another family.</i>

179
00:11:46,733 --> 00:11:48,933
<i>He just wasn't married
to the children's mother.</i>

180
00:11:49,967 --> 00:11:51,433
<i> Now it makes sense.</i>

181
00:11:52,300 --> 00:11:55,867
<i>That's why he was so confident
about marrying me.</i>

182
00:11:58,200 --> 00:11:59,567
<i> He wanted my money.</i>

183
00:12:01,167 --> 00:12:03,467
<i>He used me to support
his family.</i>

184
00:12:05,433 --> 00:12:08,333
<i>To build a business here
in the Philippines.</i>

185
00:12:09,300 --> 00:12:10,433
<i> But what hurt the most...</i>

186
00:12:11,433 --> 00:12:13,567
<i>is that even Jessica's
half-siblings...</i>

187
00:12:15,967 --> 00:12:17,300
<i> were cruel.</i>

188
00:12:19,233 --> 00:12:22,367
<i>When they found out she wasn't
really their sister,</i>

189
00:12:23,400 --> 00:12:25,267
<i> they hurt her,</i>

190
00:12:25,400 --> 00:12:26,400
<i> abused her,</i>

191
00:12:27,333 --> 00:12:29,167
<i> and mistreated her...</i>

192
00:12:29,667 --> 00:12:31,700
<i>until the child
became depressed.</i>

193
00:12:35,833 --> 00:12:37,800
<i> Until our daughter died.</i>

194
00:12:38,867 --> 00:12:40,567
<i> They had no mercy.</i>

195
00:12:40,700 --> 00:12:42,233
<i> Because of them,</i>

196
00:12:42,367 --> 00:12:45,200
<i> my child died helplessly.</i>

197
00:12:46,300 --> 00:12:47,700
<i> They're monsters.</i>

198
00:12:49,167 --> 00:12:50,700
<i> They're monsters.</i>

199
00:12:58,433 --> 00:13:00,733
Your life fell apart..

200
00:13:01,600 --> 00:13:03,133
because I wasn't there.

201
00:13:04,867 --> 00:13:06,567
But now that I'm here,

202
00:13:09,867 --> 00:13:11,433
even if Jessica is gone...

203
00:13:12,567 --> 00:13:14,067
I will avenge you.

204
00:13:17,800 --> 00:13:22,867
They will answer for everything
they did to you...

205
00:13:23,700 --> 00:13:25,267
and to Jessica.

206
00:13:28,700 --> 00:13:30,433
They will pay...

207
00:13:31,367 --> 00:13:33,133
for all of this.

208
00:13:34,800 --> 00:13:35,867
I promise.

209
00:13:43,900 --> 00:13:47,733
The PT who got you pregnant
in Saudi Arabia?

210
00:13:48,000 --> 00:13:49,133
Yes. It's him.

211
00:13:49,633 --> 00:13:50,633
Him?

212
00:13:50,967 --> 00:13:53,367
And of all places,
you meet again at Southcrest?

213
00:13:53,800 --> 00:13:55,267
And you hid it from me?

214
00:13:56,667 --> 00:13:57,633
Of course, I did.

215
00:13:58,033 --> 00:14:00,067
I know you.

216
00:14:00,200 --> 00:14:01,600
With your gossiping,

217
00:14:01,733 --> 00:14:03,233
Jojo's past in Saudi Arabia
would spread

218
00:14:03,367 --> 00:14:05,167
all over Southcrest in no time.

219
00:14:05,933 --> 00:14:07,133
Can you believe it?

220
00:14:07,267 --> 00:14:11,600
We work at the same hospital,
and I never even ran into him.

221
00:14:11,733 --> 00:14:12,667
Obviously.

222
00:14:12,967 --> 00:14:14,633
I told him to stay away
from you.

223
00:14:15,000 --> 00:14:17,100
I can't afford my plans
getting derailed.

224
00:14:17,900 --> 00:14:20,467
But you didn't
even confront him?

225
00:14:20,600 --> 00:14:21,533
No dramatic confrontation,

226
00:14:21,667 --> 00:14:23,233
no endless slaps like
in a tv drama series?

227
00:14:23,367 --> 00:14:24,400
Oh, please, Alice.

228
00:14:24,533 --> 00:14:26,467
That's too predictable.

229
00:14:26,600 --> 00:14:29,600
What would yelling
and slapping do?

230
00:14:30,100 --> 00:14:31,933
Jessica wouldn't come back.

231
00:14:32,067 --> 00:14:34,833
Instead of fighting him
and making him turn against me,

232
00:14:34,967 --> 00:14:38,067
I'll use him to get justice
for Jessica.

233
00:14:38,767 --> 00:14:41,233
I can practically smell
whatever you're cooking.

234
00:14:41,367 --> 00:14:44,233
So what kind of lies
are you feeding him?

235
00:14:45,100 --> 00:14:47,633
When I told him Jessica
was dead,

236
00:14:47,767 --> 00:14:52,300
I blamed Manuel, Felma,
and their children.

237
00:14:52,433 --> 00:14:57,233
I said that when they found out
Jessica wasn't Manuel's child,

238
00:14:57,367 --> 00:15:02,000
they abused her until she got
depressed and died.

239
00:15:02,167 --> 00:15:04,333
You're insane.

240
00:15:04,467 --> 00:15:08,767
They didn't even know who
Jessica's real father was.

241
00:15:08,900 --> 00:15:10,300
That's for me to handle.

242
00:15:12,200 --> 00:15:16,467
What matters right now is
that Jojo believes me.

243
00:15:17,167 --> 00:15:20,833
That he helps me get revenge
for my daughter.

244
00:15:21,767 --> 00:15:23,833
I'm fueling his anger more.

245
00:15:24,967 --> 00:15:26,033
And it's working.

246
00:15:26,167 --> 00:15:27,633
Do you know what he did?

247
00:15:27,767 --> 00:15:31,067
He did everything he could
to become Felma's PT.

248
00:15:31,200 --> 00:15:32,600
I swear, I don't get you.

249
00:15:32,733 --> 00:15:34,833
But where is this going?

250
00:15:35,767 --> 00:15:37,800
Once you get revenge for
Jessica,

251
00:15:37,933 --> 00:15:39,733
are you and Jojo getting back
together?

252
00:15:41,167 --> 00:15:42,200
Are you serious, Alice?

253
00:15:42,333 --> 00:15:46,600
After he ruined my life,
you think I'd want him?

254
00:15:47,433 --> 00:15:48,800
This is purely business.

255
00:15:49,133 --> 00:15:50,233
Nothing personal.

256
00:15:51,867 --> 00:15:52,667
Ma'am, let's stand up.

257
00:15:52,800 --> 00:15:54,267
Hold onto my shoulder.

258
00:15:56,833 --> 00:15:57,567
Okay.

259
00:15:57,700 --> 00:15:59,167
One, two, three.

260
00:15:59,300 --> 00:16:00,233
Up!

261
00:16:00,367 --> 00:16:01,833
Good, good.

262
00:16:01,967 --> 00:16:03,533
Hold here, Ma'am.

263
00:16:06,433 --> 00:16:07,300
Okay.

264
00:16:07,900 --> 00:16:09,833
Are you feeling dizzy?

265
00:16:10,433 --> 00:16:11,433
Any headache?

266
00:16:11,567 --> 00:16:12,900
None?

267
00:16:13,033 --> 00:16:14,567
Okay, Ma'am.

268
00:16:14,700 --> 00:16:19,700
Let's start by stepping
with your right foot.

269
00:16:19,833 --> 00:16:21,433
Slowly, Ma'am.

270
00:16:21,567 --> 00:16:22,367
Go on.

271
00:16:22,500 --> 00:16:24,033
If it's too much, we stop.

272
00:16:24,167 --> 00:16:25,967
Okay, take it easy, Ma'am.

273
00:16:26,100 --> 00:16:26,933
Good, Ma'am.

274
00:16:27,667 --> 00:16:29,067
Your balance is
much better now.

275
00:16:29,200 --> 00:16:33,633
You're not dizzy,
you're not swaying.

276
00:16:33,767 --> 00:16:34,933
Great job.

277
00:16:35,067 --> 00:16:42,800
I'm motivated to get better

278
00:16:42,967 --> 00:16:45,433
because of my kids
and their father.

279
00:16:47,167 --> 00:16:52,500
And the therapists
here are so kind.

280
00:16:52,633 --> 00:16:55,967
They really encourage me.

281
00:16:56,100 --> 00:16:57,900
That's nice to hear, Ma'am.

282
00:16:58,033 --> 00:16:59,867
It's true.

283
00:17:00,000 --> 00:17:09,233
I feel safe and confident
with all of you here.

284
00:17:10,333 --> 00:17:20,300
I told Manuel to continue
his therapy here.

285
00:17:22,133 --> 00:17:27,867
Of course, I want you
handling him

286
00:17:28,000 --> 00:17:32,233
while I'm in my other sessions.

287
00:17:32,367 --> 00:17:34,033
Of course, Ma'am.

288
00:17:34,167 --> 00:17:38,300
I'm more than willing
to guide both of you.

289
00:17:38,433 --> 00:17:41,467
Thank you, Sir Jojo.

290
00:17:43,333 --> 00:17:44,467
Please, Ma'am. Just Jojo.

291
00:17:44,600 --> 00:17:45,300
That's embarrassing.

292
00:17:47,367 --> 00:17:49,167
All right,
careful with your steps.

293
00:17:49,333 --> 00:17:54,767
I want to go home soon
and fully recover

294
00:17:54,900 --> 00:17:59,600
so I can be with my family
this Christmas.

295
00:18:01,433 --> 00:18:08,233
<i>While I will never experience
Christmas with my child.</i>

296
00:18:08,367 --> 00:18:10,767
<i> Because you killed her.</i>

297
00:18:10,900 --> 00:18:13,033
<i>So you and Manuel
had better be ready,</i>

298
00:18:13,167 --> 00:18:15,267
<i> especially your children.</i>

299
00:18:20,067 --> 00:18:21,200
Felma, I've got it.

300
00:18:21,333 --> 00:18:21,900
I've got it.

301
00:18:22,067 --> 00:18:22,933
I've got it.

302
00:18:24,467 --> 00:18:26,333
You might cut yourself.

303
00:18:26,467 --> 00:18:27,800
No.

304
00:18:27,933 --> 00:18:29,867
I can handle it.

305
00:18:30,600 --> 00:18:31,867
Looks like you can.

306
00:18:33,700 --> 00:18:36,200
You know, it looks like
I'm not needed here anymore.

307
00:18:36,333 --> 00:18:38,233
I'll head back
to Davao for now.

308
00:18:38,367 --> 00:18:39,867
My flight is tonight.

309
00:18:40,000 --> 00:18:41,967
Wait, it'd be a waste
if you're not with us

310
00:18:42,100 --> 00:18:42,800
this Christmas.

311
00:18:46,600 --> 00:18:55,733
The doctor said once I improve,

312
00:18:56,333 --> 00:19:04,967
I can go home and celebrate
Christmas there.

313
00:19:06,667 --> 00:19:11,133
All right then, I'll do my best
to come back for Christmas.

314
00:19:11,267 --> 00:19:12,000
Yes, you should.

315
00:19:12,133 --> 00:19:14,167
So we can all celebrate
together.

316
00:19:14,300 --> 00:19:17,267
And so we can thank you
for everything you've done

317
00:19:17,400 --> 00:19:19,500
for our family,
especially for Felma.

318
00:19:22,633 --> 00:19:32,600
Noah, we can never
thank you enough.

319
00:19:35,667 --> 00:19:38,867
Actually, the pleasure is mine.

320
00:19:43,400 --> 00:19:44,967
Sir, let's do our exercise now.

321
00:19:45,100 --> 00:19:46,567
Just step over here.

322
00:19:46,700 --> 00:19:50,133
Slowly, so your balance stays
stable.

323
00:19:50,267 --> 00:19:51,033
Just like this.

324
00:19:51,667 --> 00:19:52,767
That's it.

325
00:19:58,767 --> 00:19:59,733
That's it.

326
00:20:02,267 --> 00:20:03,267
There you go.

327
00:20:03,967 --> 00:20:05,667
Go ahead, Sir. Go slowly.

328
00:20:09,767 --> 00:20:11,267
Do you have a family, Jo?

329
00:20:12,967 --> 00:20:13,967
Oh, Sir...

330
00:20:14,800 --> 00:20:16,100
I was never married.

331
00:20:17,067 --> 00:20:18,833
I even lost a child.

332
00:20:19,967 --> 00:20:21,867
But let's not talk about that.

333
00:20:23,167 --> 00:20:24,533
Looks like we're the same.

334
00:20:25,400 --> 00:20:26,633
I lost a child, too.

335
00:20:28,167 --> 00:20:29,133
Her name's Jessica.

336
00:20:31,967 --> 00:20:34,967
Sir, what happened to her?

337
00:20:38,367 --> 00:20:39,400
It was an accident.

338
00:20:40,667 --> 00:20:41,833
She was hit by a car.

339
00:20:43,400 --> 00:20:44,833
Poor child.

340
00:20:45,700 --> 00:20:47,067
She was so kind.

341
00:20:48,000 --> 00:20:49,367
Very caring.

342
00:20:50,600 --> 00:20:53,200
That's why I loved
my youngest so much.

343
00:20:56,267 --> 00:21:00,167
Sir, was the person
responsible jailed?

344
00:21:02,367 --> 00:21:03,833
Yes. He's in prison now.

345
00:21:08,133 --> 00:21:12,067
Was Jessica your child
with Miss Felma?

346
00:21:14,433 --> 00:21:15,700
That's a long story.

347
00:21:19,467 --> 00:21:20,400
She was from my wife.

348
00:21:20,533 --> 00:21:24,500
But I was just forced
to marry her.

349
00:21:24,633 --> 00:21:26,333
Felma is the one I truly love.

350
00:21:30,767 --> 00:21:33,233
Sir, I'm sorry.

351
00:21:34,333 --> 00:21:37,567
That question got too personal.

352
00:21:38,333 --> 00:21:39,333
It's all right.

353
00:21:39,800 --> 00:21:41,400
I've got nothing to hide.

354
00:21:51,900 --> 00:21:53,767
The nerve of that man.

355
00:21:53,900 --> 00:21:56,633
Manuel has a lot of nerve.

356
00:21:56,767 --> 00:21:59,467
Yes. He never loved me.

357
00:21:59,600 --> 00:22:01,133
He only loved my money.

358
00:22:01,267 --> 00:22:02,333
That's all he wanted.

359
00:22:04,933 --> 00:22:08,667
He's lucky I still
see him as a patient.

360
00:22:09,633 --> 00:22:11,000
If I wanted to...

361
00:22:12,500 --> 00:22:16,133
I could cripple him permanently.

362
00:22:18,300 --> 00:22:19,600
But I'm confused.

363
00:22:21,600 --> 00:22:24,967
You said Manuel was cruel
to Jessica.

364
00:22:25,100 --> 00:22:31,233
So why is he saying that
he loved our child so much?

365
00:22:31,700 --> 00:22:32,733
Of course.

366
00:22:32,867 --> 00:22:34,100
You think he'd admit
to other people

367
00:22:34,233 --> 00:22:36,367
that he mistreated Jessica?

368
00:22:36,500 --> 00:22:37,400
Come on.

369
00:22:40,000 --> 00:22:45,533
That's why it hurts so much
every time I hear Manuel's lies.

370
00:22:54,800 --> 00:22:56,433
Inhale...

371
00:22:56,567 --> 00:22:57,167
Exhale.

372
00:22:57,300 --> 00:22:58,467
Okay, okay. One step.

373
00:22:58,600 --> 00:22:59,900
One more.

374
00:23:00,500 --> 00:23:01,433
Inhale.

375
00:23:02,000 --> 00:23:03,000
Okay, Sir.

376
00:23:03,500 --> 00:23:04,533
Exhale.

377
00:23:04,667 --> 00:23:05,733
Inhale.

378
00:23:05,867 --> 00:23:06,733
You good?

379
00:23:06,867 --> 00:23:08,933
Okay.

380
00:23:09,967 --> 00:23:11,100
Slowly, Sir.

381
00:23:14,200 --> 00:23:15,867
It might hurt a bit, okay?

382
00:23:16,000 --> 00:23:16,900
Okay...

383
00:23:17,033 --> 00:23:17,767
Okay.

384
00:23:17,900 --> 00:23:18,767
Slowly.

385
00:23:18,900 --> 00:23:19,900
Can you do it, Sir?

386
00:23:20,167 --> 00:23:21,200
You can do it.

387
00:23:21,867 --> 00:23:22,833
Step.

388
00:23:23,067 --> 00:23:23,667
Okay.

389
00:23:24,500 --> 00:23:26,733
Okay.

390
00:23:26,867 --> 00:23:27,867
You good?

391
00:23:28,000 --> 00:23:28,933
Good.

392
00:23:29,067 --> 00:23:30,000
That's it.

393
00:23:30,133 --> 00:23:31,333
Good.

394
00:23:33,867 --> 00:23:35,033
Sir! Sir!

395
00:23:35,167 --> 00:23:36,433
Are you okay?

396
00:23:36,567 --> 00:23:37,633
- Wait.
- I'm okay.

397
00:23:37,767 --> 00:23:38,433
Let's relax a bit.

398
00:23:41,233 --> 00:23:42,267
- Are you okay, Sir?
- Okay.

399
00:23:42,400 --> 00:23:43,133
You all right, Sir? No pain?

400
00:23:43,267 --> 00:23:45,467
Yeah. I just lost my balance.

401
00:23:46,467 --> 00:23:49,100
Sir, let's try 12 reps first,
okay?

402
00:23:49,233 --> 00:23:51,000
- Sure.
- Okay, Sir.

403
00:23:51,133 --> 00:23:54,467
If there's pain, we stop, okay?

404
00:23:54,600 --> 00:23:55,933
- Okay.
- All right. Let's go.

405
00:23:57,833 --> 00:23:58,867
Inhale.

406
00:23:59,000 --> 00:23:59,633
Exhale.

407
00:23:59,767 --> 00:24:00,567
One.

408
00:24:00,700 --> 00:24:01,633
Inhale.

409
00:24:02,200 --> 00:24:03,200
Two...

410
00:24:04,467 --> 00:24:05,133
three...

411
00:24:15,333 --> 00:24:16,567
What if Manuel actually died?

412
00:24:16,700 --> 00:24:17,400
Tell me!

413
00:24:17,533 --> 00:24:19,300
Why is your reaction so extreme?

414
00:24:19,433 --> 00:24:20,333
Do you still love him?

415
00:24:20,467 --> 00:24:21,700
Is that why
you're so worried?

416
00:24:21,833 --> 00:24:22,733
It's really different, isn't it?

417
00:24:22,867 --> 00:24:25,000
When the mother is here.

418
00:24:25,133 --> 00:24:27,167
Nothing compares to
the warmth Mom brings.

419
00:24:27,300 --> 00:24:30,800
What matters is we're all
together this Christmas.

420
00:24:30,967 --> 00:24:32,933
Jojo, Merry Christmas!

421
00:24:33,067 --> 00:24:35,267
- Merry Christmas.
- And thank you, by the way.

422
00:24:35,400 --> 00:24:38,633
Mom and Dad have improved
so much because of you.

423
00:24:38,767 --> 00:24:40,067
Oh, it's nothing.

424
00:24:40,200 --> 00:24:40,933
Come in.

425
00:24:41,067 --> 00:24:43,533
Let's have snacks.

426
00:24:43,667 --> 00:24:44,733
Jessica?

427
00:24:44,867 --> 00:24:46,700
Do you know our youngest sister?
